===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#(''slang, used [[hyperbolically]]'') An unspecified large number (of).
#:'''quotations'''
#:*"It'll just take a '''squillion''' times longer than the age of the universe to happen." &mdash; [http://groups-beta.google.com/group/talk.origins/msg/5badfa4e62401959]
#:*"I just ran the numbers and got 1.7 '''squillion''', myself. " &mdash; [http://groups-beta.google.com/group/talk.origins/msg/a79427654911dcfa]

====Quotations====
*'''1990''' — [[w:Terry Pratchett|Terry Pratchett]], ''Eric'', p 138
*:"You thinks to yourself, 'There's a billion, trillion '''squillion''' of them, no one's going to notice.'  But that's where professionalism comes in, sort of thing."

